1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,530
Believing they will succeed, and that it's not impossible, these folks study and observe the behavior of senior executives.

2
00:00:08,959 --> 00:00:13,330
They learn how successful people approach problems and make decisions.

3
00:00:13,599 --> 00:00:16,770
They observe the attitudes of successful people.

4
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:22,370
The how-to-do-it always comes to the person who believes he can do it.

5
00:00:23,039 --> 00:00:31,169
A young woman I am acquainted with decided two years ago that she was going to establish a sales agency to sell mobile homes.

6
00:00:31,440 --> 00:00:35,970
She was advised by many that she shouldn't and couldn't do it.

7
00:00:36,239 --> 00:00:44,690
She had less than three thousand dollars in savings and was advised that the minimum capital investment required was many times that.

8
00:00:45,199 --> 00:00:48,289
Look how competitive it is," she was advised.

9
00:00:48,399 --> 00:00:56,930
And besides, what practical experience have you had in selling mobile homes, let alone managing a business?" her advisors asked.

10
00:00:57,359 --> 00:01:01,970
But this young lady had belief in herself and her ability to succeed.

11
00:01:02,159 --> 00:01:09,009
She quickly admitted that she lacked capital, that the business was very competitive, and that she lacked experience.

12
00:01:09,440 --> 00:01:16,610
But, she said, all the evidence I can gather shows that the mobile home industry is going to expand.

13
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:19,970
On top of that, I've studied my competition.

14
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:25,649
I know I can do a better job of merchandising trailers than anybody else in this town.

15
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:30,610
I expect to make some mistakes, but I'm going to be on top in a hurry.

16
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,370
And she was.

17
00:01:32,639 --> 00:01:34,930
She had little trouble getting capital.

18
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:42,530
Her absolutely unquestioned belief that she could succeed with this business won her the confidence of two investors.

19
00:01:42,719 --> 00:01:46,769
And armed with complete belief, she did the impossible.

20
00:01:46,880 --> 00:01:52,610
She got a trailer manufacturer to advance her a limited inventory with no money down.

21
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:58,050
Last year, she sold over one million dollars worth of trailers.

22
00:01:58,719 --> 00:02:03,649
Next year, she says, I expect to gross over $2 million.

23
00:02:04,399 --> 00:02:11,089
Belief, strong belief, triggers the mind to figure ways and means and how to.

24
00:02:11,199 --> 00:02:15,569
And believing you can succeed makes others place confidence in you.

25
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:24,370
Most people do not put much stock in belief, but some, the residents of Successfulville, U.S.A., do.

